				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: just how many aoe often?<a name="59899"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 1 04 8:17 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well AEing is still very nice if you dont have much time and want to get a bit of XP. So I dont really AE too often but when I have a bit of spare time inbetween I like to use it that way.
<br />
For example if at 65 you collect all flies/rats/larvas of the islands and kite them at the usual spot, you need maybe 15 mins and get 35% AA XP which isnt too shabby. Of course all the flies are gone then and you will have to wait for them to repop and that will slow you down quite a bit. But it's nice for just logging on for 15 mins and logging out again after.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />
The risk isn't too high as you should survive when the swarm hits you. (My PC lacks some RAM and lags badly sometimes and I end up getting hit by the swarm up to 5 times a single kite. Equipment is rather crappy as well, so  think as an average lvl 65 player you have a good chance of surviving enemy contact. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />)
<br />
Yes I agree there are a lot more efficient ways of XPing, but you have the advantage of being able to start immediately without preperation (group organisation etc.) and knowing it only takes 15 mins. In addition it's fun and offers a certain challenge.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />
</span></td>
