				<td colspan="2"><span>I do some AE kiting in Nadox for a variety of things.  I use it to finish off an AA I might be 10-20% away from during the previous evening's group, if I need 1 more AA to get that 9-12 point ability I've been saving up for, or for 500-1k in pp to help fund my next set of tradeskill combines.  
<br />

<br />
If I get to Nadox and anyone is fighting any of the luggards (where I do my kiting) I leave and come back later.  If some named pops from my kite and I don't need it, I offer the items to anyone who might be in the zone.  Being nice and not imposing on anyone elses' game makes people not care about it much.  I've even done a kite or two for that 48 cleric trying to get to 49 so he could get his new spells.
<br />

<br />
Is AE kiting overpowered?  A bit.  Is it completely risk-free?  No.  Does every bard out there do it?  No.  Do a couple of prick bards trying to do it cause grief which leads to people complaining about it?  Yes.
<br />

