				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: just how many aoe often?<a name="59966"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 1 04 2:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I do not AoE kite for XPs.  I have in past, and out of pure stubborness, and the desire to have all the bardly tricks in my bag, I got to the point that I could be successful at it.
<br />

<br />
I never got to the point that I could ENJOY it.  Its too tight tolerances for me.. too far.. missing mobs with the song.. too close  not BEING missed by the mobs... running the same tight pattern ad nauseum.  Not my cup of tea.
<br />

<br />
With swarming I got very similar levels of XP per hour, more if I messed up the AoE kite at all, at a LOT lower risk and a lot more reliability.  
<br />

<br />
But now here I am at 65, and folks are talking about some wonderful XP returns with AOE.  I have been tempted to re-try my hand at it sometime.  But this thread has convinced me that it probably isn't worth it:
<br />
1. Yes in 15 minutes you get more XPs than I can swarming... but...
<br />
2. All your mobs are gone and you have to wait for them to respawn.  Waiting is not what bards are meant to do.
<br />
3. Seems CR impinges on the XP per hour number quite a bit, its seldom a problem for me while swarming, barring LD, or very poorly timed lag, which would kill me AOEing too.
<br />
4. Swarming... I don't kill as many at a pop, but I kill constantly, with looting being the only thing that slows me down.
<br />

<br />
So since I am already outpacing most of my guild and other friends with AA's, I think I am gonna forego AOE and stick to swarming when I choose to solo.  I'll leave my mind open, but I got a plan for now.  With larger blocks of time I will group or raid, with small blocks of time I will swarm.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
