				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: just how many aoe often?<a name="59973"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 1 04 3:25 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Once upon a time, the thought of a turn key freebie method of auto kiting, using auto circle came to light. Then the swarms of people came to see the post on the exactness of how they might actually gather up a bunch of mobs and then just tap a button at leisure for experience.  Problem was it was not easy and that is why we have been plauged with &quot;auto circle how too's&quot; for the last 6 months.
<br />

<br />
Some that have never kited want to know how to get, what is in their mind, massive freebie mindless experience.  Then they post how they died and want to know the REAL secret, only to be told to reread the guide on how to.  Pathetic circle really of how do we, i died, how do we.
<br />

<br />
I am pretty sure that if it was turn key, you read a post and get an aa every 30 minsutes, it would have been a problem.  Just the fact that people repeatedly post I am not getting it means that it is in fact not turn key easy.
<br />

<br />
So the posts and air time are as a result of some bards who had there eyes light up on this dreamy fake hope.  
<br />

<br />
Maybe in a few months it will go away....lets face it sooner or later when all are 65, auto circling a bunch of low blues might not seem like the thing to do anyways.  
<br />

<br />
I have kited every possible way we Bards can kite, and I still do not get the Auto bit.  My advice would be do something else with your time, or if you want to really rake in the aa, learn the Manual area kite and kill for an aa every 20 to 30 mins.  It won't be a free ride though, and if you though auto was tuff, well manual is tuffer.
<br />

<br />
(assuming you had ALL the information on the Auto method).  Most tend to leave you hanging with the most important information, being what mod is required for each mob type.  Then again if the method is in a guide, go and experiment and get what you want.  Expect the whole game to be a free ride?
<br />

<br />
Need nerfing..NO
<br />

<br />
How many do it..lots try, probably 10% area somewhat frequently, very few manual.
<br />

<br />
Do some disrupt lowbie experience zones...Yes, and this is the real problem as far as a GM might be concerned.  It isn't the class balance, it is the play nice, or be an a$ type game play that really has this up for talks.
<br />

<br />
Area is not a problem, if you really want it to be one, it will be at the hands of 10 or so Bards per server that take over entire zones and disrupt others from gaining group experience.  Now that is not going to happen right?  It would have been nerfed (oh wait it was allready) long ago if it was our class and broken for our favour.
<br />

<br />
Lastly, pre nerf of extended notes was there a problem...yeah, but they fixed it.  Previously any person with a pulse and the time could aa massive ammounts with absolutely ZERO risk.  Take some Risk now and go try, then report back about how you died.  Just like what is posted every day now.  Go try, because there is nothing left about tecnique to even talk about anymore!  It has all been said.
<br />

<br />
Moose  
<br />
</span></td>
